Rule: Some set of operations that can be applicable for group of resources. There are different
API Groups 
- v1/ apps/v1 batch/a1

Role, Cluster Role: Roles consists of Rules. The difference is scope. 
- If you apply rules for
- A single namespace then it is called as Role.
- If a rule is applied for whole cluster then it is called as ClusterRole

Subject: Who is going to perform operation on Kubernetes is called a Subject.
    Users: Like you and me
    Service Accounts: Jenkins, Helm 
    Groups: Groups are for multiple accounts

RoleBinding, ClusterRoleBinding: Binds subject(s) to the Roles.






